	explore and look around in.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	[Wave]Might have to extend my trip by[BR]
	a couple weeks if I'm not careful.[Wait][End]
}

#message:07:032
{
	[Style Right]
	After some browsing, I learnt that[BR]
	[SaveColor][Color:05]Kinoko Town[RestoreColor]'s native instrument is[BR]
	the pan flute.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	A pan flute would be an [PrintRising]excellent[BR]
	gift[/fx] to take home and display in[BR]
	my office. [Pause 15]It couldn't hurt to learn[BR]
	how to play it.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	That's just scratching the surface.[BR]
	[Pause 10][SaveColor][Color:05]Koopa Village[RestoreColor] and [SaveColor][Color:08]Dry Dry Outpost[RestoreColor][BR]
	also have interesting towns to[BR]
	explore and look around in.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	[Wave]Might have to extend my trip by[BR]
	a couple weeks if I'm not careful.[Wait][End]
}

#message:07:033
{
	[Style Right]
	This wasn't written in any of the[BR]
	travel pamphlets.[BR]
	[Pause 15]Dark, nauseous smoke that clouds[BR]
	[SaveColor][Color:05]Kinoko Town[RestoreColor]?[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	I should probably call a navy in[BR]
	fear of my health,[Pause 10] but it's just so[BR]
	unique[Pause 3] [PrintGrowing]and interesting...[/fx][Wait][End]
}

#message:07:034
{
	[Style Right]
	Let me tell you a story.[BR]
	[Pause 5]Many decades ago there was[BR]
	a land known as Bengteng.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	This was of course the home[BR]
	of all Bob-Omb folk.[BR]
	[Pause 10]They lived happily...[BR]
	[Pause 10]For a while anyway.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Back over in Koopa Village,[BR]
	the Coop Notes were up to no[BR]
	good, being menaces to society.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	One day, the higher ups of the[BR]
	village decided enough is enough[BR]
	and booted the Coop Notes out of[BR]
	the village.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	With no where to go, the Coop[BR]
	Notes sought to terrorize the[BR]
	local land of Bengteng.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Those poor, innocent Bob-Ombs[BR]
	had done nothing wrong either.[BR]
	[Pause 15]In fact,[Pause 5] the Koopas and[BR]
	Bob-Ombs were comrades.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	The Coop Notes built their own[BR]
	stronghold; a place where nobody[BR]
	could have authority.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	And so they enslaved the[BR]
	Bob-Ombs residents of Bengteng[BR]
	and made them work labour.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Naturally, this made the Bob-[BR]
	Ombs resent the Coop Notes[BR]
	heavily.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	It seems that story has changed[BR]
	since you've arrived.[BR]
	[Pause 10]You're a true keeper of[BR]
	history, my friend.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Send my regards to both the[BR]
	Koopas and Bob-Ombs, okay?[Wait][End]
}

