#message:07:036
{
	[Style Right]
	I have another story for ya.[BR]
	[Pause 10]A long time ago, Dry Dry Outpost[BR]
	was founded by a tribe of Little[BR]
	Mousers.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	It was hundreds of years ago.[BR]
	[Pause 10]Back then, the sands of the[BR]
	desert were arid and yellow.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Nowadays I'm sure you're aware[BR]
	that the sands have moistened and[BR]
	turned a fragrant purple.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Everyone always asks the same[BR]
	question:[Pause 10] "Why's the sand purple?"[BR]
	[Pause 15]Due to a defect in the moonlight,[BR]
	the sand reacts in strange ways.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	The moon refracted off the sand,[BR]
	and in a confused state, [Pause 5]the[BR]
	molecules of the sand particles[BR]
	shifted to a different colour.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	To this day, scientists can't[BR]
	glean the logic of it at all.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	The Mouser tribe were the original[BR]
	founders, [Pause 5]but one day, the king of[BR]
	the Mouser tribe approached the[BR]
	prince of the Dryites.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	With similar goals in mind to assemble[BR]
	a desert civilization, they shook hands[BR]
	and built what's now known as [SaveColor][Color:08]Dry Dry[BR]
	Outpost[RestoreColor].[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Besides the sand, not much has[BR]
	changed. The town remains fairly[BR]
	old-timey.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Come back later and I'll[BR]
	have more to say.[Wait][End]
}

#message:07:037
{
	[Style Right]
	You guessed it. Another story.[BR]
	This time it's about the land[BR]
	of [SaveColor][Color:03]Gusty Gulch[RestoreColor] as well as[BR]
	the haunted [SaveColor][Color:07]Forever Forest[RestoreColor].[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Let's start with [SaveColor][Color:07]Forever Forest[RestoreColor].[BR]
	Mayoi no Mori, the hellish woods[BR]
	of souls who scream in pain.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	In olden times, that was [SaveColor][Color:07]Forever[BR]
	Forest[RestoreColor]'s true name, but it was[BR]
	deemed too violent to be passed[BR]
	on to our kids.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Boos have been around for a very[BR]
	long time as well.[BR]
	[Pause 10]You know Lady Bow, the princess[BR]
	of [SaveColor][Color:07]Boo's Mansion Royalty Estate[RestoreColor].[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Their ancestry dates back at[BR]
	least a couple thousand years.[BR]
	[Pause 10]A septette is performed upon[BR]
	hailing of every princess.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	The oldest known princess of[BR]
	Boo regality is Lady Yuyuresa.[BR]
	[Pause 10]Yuyuresa Ojou-sama defined what[BR]
	it meant to be a Boo.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	[SaveColor][Color:03]Gusty Gulch[RestoreColor] used to be a grassland[BR]
	full of pretty flowers, but a grand[BR]
	flood and sandstorm swept up the[BR]
	land and turned it to ruins.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Some Boos weren't fit to live[BR]
	alongside the princesses, so they[BR]
	opted to live there.[BR]
	[Wait][Next]
	Drat! I'm out of time.[BR]
	I'll get a new story soon.
	[Wait][End]
}

